summary.name: Bacteria_Antibiotic_Sensitivity
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about the sensitivity of various bacteria to different antibiotics, including Penicillin, Streptomycin, and Neomycin. It also includes the Gram staining classification and the genus of each bacterium.

properties.description: The name of the bacterium species.
The sensitivity of the bacterium to Penicillin, measured in micrograms per milliliter (µg/mL).
The sensitivity of the bacterium to Streptomycin, measured in micrograms per milliliter (µg/mL).
The sensitivity of the bacterium to Neomycin, measured in micrograms per milliliter (µg/mL).
The Gram staining classification of the bacterium, either positive or negative.

goals.question: What is the distribution of Penicillin sensitivity among the bacteria?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of Penicillin sensitivity among the different bacteria and identify any outliers or patterns.

goals.question: How does the sensitivity of bacteria to Streptomycin compare to their sensitivity to Neomycin?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of Streptomycin sensitivity vs Neomycin sensitivity
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any correlation or patterns between the sensitivity of bacteria to Streptomycin and Neomycin.

goals.question: What is the distribution of Gram staining classification among the bacteria?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of Gram staining classification
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the proportion of bacteria that are Gram-positive or Gram-negative.

goals.question: Which genus of bacteria is most sensitive to Penicillin?
goals.visualization: Box plot of Penicillin sensitivity by genus
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any differences in Penicillin sensitivity among the different genera of bacteria.

goals.question: Is there a relationship between the sensitivity of bacteria to Penicillin and their Gram staining classification?
goals.visualization: Box plot of Penicillin sensitivity by Gram staining classification
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any differences in Penicillin sensitivity between Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Penicillin', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin sensitivity among the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
